<item>
            <title>[FELIX-366] Bound Service Replacement incorrect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-366</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently SCR implements incorrect bound service replacement for references of unary cardinality: Instead of first binding the new (replacement) service and then unbinding the old (outgoing) service, the old service is first unbound and then the replacement bound. This violates the specification in section 112.5.10, Bound Service Replacement, of the Declarative Services Specification.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
